{"tid":2320821,"cid":5,"subCid":10,"title":"澳洲人發起 杯葛41間中資擁有的酒莊","createTime":"2020-12-11T05:51:09.000Z","updateTime":"2020-12-13T08:22:44.000Z","uid":48083,"like":66,"dislike":1,"uniUserReply":17,"replies":[{"pid":"d9ddd0020ec9b6478fe1dda6b54185e4897508a9","tid":2320821,"uid":48083,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-12-11T05:51:09.000Z","msg":"名單話係fb流傳但揾唔到<br />\n<br />\nAussies urged to boycott 41 vineyards actually owned by Chinese firms<br />\n<br />\nThe explosive list was shared on social media recently following Beijing&rsquo;s escalating feud with Australia.<br />\n<br />\nIt has led to a raft of devastating restrictions to be imposed upon Australian industries, with the wine industry especially hard hit by new import taxes of up to a staggering 212 per cent.<br />\n<br />\nOther industries already affected by Beijing&rsquo;s bullying include timber, lamb, lobster and barley, and there are fears the tactics could spread even further to other sectors.<br />\n<br />\nThe list, which was shared on the Vino e Amigos Facebook page, reveals that most of the nation&rsquo;s Chinese-owned vineyards are located in Victoria and South Australia, with some also found in Tasmania, WA and NSW.<br />\n<br />\nHowever, it does not reveal crucial details such as what percentage of each winery is owned by Chinese companies, and many social media users pointed out it included some wineries owned by Australian-Chinese people who weren&rsquo;t to blame for Beijing&rsquo;s tactics.<br />\n<br />\nAnother pointed out some on the list were &ldquo;run by Aussie workers though, and Aussie workers are still getting paid&rdquo;, indicating a boycott may cause more harm than good.<br />\n<br />\nBut the long list shocked many Facebook users, with dozens unaware of just how many Australian-based companies weren&rsquo;t actually Australian-owned.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;No wonder some Aussies always say the govt is selling the country to China,&rdquo; one person posted, while another added: &ldquo;Aussie winemakers have been teaching the Chinese how to make wine for years. For what, to screw us over?&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://amp.news.com.au/finance/business/other-industries/aussies-urged-to-boycott-41-vineyards-actually-owned-by-chinese-firms/news-story/c7cd6724a093e37cc7b51bce1b3a8c58\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Famp.news.com.au%2Ffinance%2Fbusiness%2Fother-industries%2Faussies-urged-to-boycott-41-vineyards-actually-owned-by-chinese-firms%2Fnews-story%2Fc7cd6724a093e37cc7b51bce1b3a8c58&d=%2B91LnCbTcEAXcT2WrppvqYleFUCahE4vUWSiCYLfmAs%3D&h=7a471a1e\" target=\"_blank\">https://amp.news.com.au/finance/business/other-industries/aussies-urged-to-boycott-41-vineyards-actually-owned-by-chinese-firms/news-story/c7cd6724a093e37cc7b51bce1b3a8c58</a>"},{"pid":"d2cb3c2e5ba73498a53d3e171c1806aeacc82b59","tid":2320821,"uid":73381,"like":3,"dislike":3,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-12-11T05:52:36.000Z","msg":"五毛勿回<br />\n<br />\n誠懇呼籲唔好再舉美國旗，你唔係美國人又搞佢哋支旗，美國人會好反感<br />\n<a href=\"https://lih.kg/1319023\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://lih.kg/1319023</a><br />\n- 分享自 LIHKG 討論區"},{"pid":"6795173b8789829e4e23f017a1a9364948d08c28","tid":2320821,"uid":48083,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":3,"replyTime":"2020-12-11T05:54:44.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/angel.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/angel.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"f17a327a0b773917d1f9970cd5e79b36d0a8d664","tid":2320821,"uid":73381,"like":1,"dislike":2,"score":-1,"quote":{"pid":"6795173b8789829e4e23f017a1a9364948d08c28","tid":2320821,"uid":48083,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":3,"replyTime":"2020-12-11T05:54:44.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/angel.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/angel.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-12-11T05:55:29.000Z","msg":"傻西<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"h